      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a preserved example of high-revving precision. At its heart is the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing for razor-sharp throttle response. The power is managed by a tactile 6-speed Getrag manual transmission and sent to the rear wheels through a factory M Variable Differential Lock. The chassis is exceptionally sorted, with the critical rear subframe reinforcement already addressed and the suspension geometry maintained to factory specifications. Every bushing, seal, and mechanical component reflects a standard of care that preserves the original driving dynamics. Finished in Carbon Black over Nappa leather, this specimen offers impeccable compression numbers and an untouched engine bay, representing the pinnacle of naturally aspirated performance.",
